The paper deals with the Multi-Agent Pickup and Delivery (MAPD) problem, which is a subfield of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel algorithm for path planning that takes into account kinematic constraints of real robots, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also uses advanced data structures and combinatorial search algorithms, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
